-- Indian shares end lower; Infosys falls 7.9 pct
-- By Indulal PM
-- Thu May 29, 2014 06:18AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 29 (Reuters) - India's NSE index posted its biggest daily fall in nearly four months, declining for a third session in four, as Infosys slumped after its president resigned, while profit-taking continued to hit shares from record highs earlier this month.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally closed 1.31 percent lower at 24,234.15, while the broader NSE index <.NSEI> ended 1.14 percent down at 7,246.20.